9:
You can carry on the way you have,
or return to your real family.
19:
It might be more correct to say they
contacted us.
21:
They seem to be a family
well-versed in the field of magical
research. Apparently, they heard a
rumor that I was at the academy.
30:
...Maybe it's just taking a while to sink
in.
32:
It looks like they want me to quit the
Academy and rejoin the family.
37: ...But why now, after all this time?
41:
I was told that it would be trouble for
them if I did not return.
44:
Their successor disappeared, then
they happened to find out that I was
doing research at the Academy.
48: So because it's convenient for them...
57:
...Honestly? Yes. I'm on the fence
over what to do.
60:
I believe it's important to choose my
own path. But if I could do
something that would make my
biological family happy...
63:
If I could be of use to them after all
this time... I can hardly think of
anything else I'd rather do.
74:
This is no trivial decision. Taking your
time seems appropriate to me.
78:
E-Ernest! Come to the orphanage,
quick!
79:
Some weird guys just showed up.
They said they were your...
assistants...
82: Ernest. We have come to collect you.
85:
...I haven't given my answer yet.
Showing up like this will upset the
children.
88:
...Do you have any doubts, sir? This is
your chance to start your life over.
94:
I don't get what the problem is at all.
I guess growing up in a dump like
this really does things to your brain...
102:
Denying these children their dignity
is the only thing I will stop you from
doing.
105:
Huh? That's some big talk coming
from an illegitimate son.
108:
D-don't you dare bully Ernest! You'll
have to go through me if you don't
let up!
110:
Yeah, you can't just say stuff like
that! We love Ernest, and we won't
let you hurt him!
117:
...Nothing will change your past, but
you're free to make whatever
decision you want for your future.
123: Yes. It's going to be okay, Ernest.
131:
Thank you... I'm okay now. I've made
up my mind.
135:
I won't be returning to my original
home.
138:
But being the greedy man I am, I
don't want you to be my enemies,
either.
140:
I have a proposition to make. Why
don't we discuss it over tea?
144:
Don't tell me you're still not
convinced, Father.
147:
...Working with these out-of-touch
fools would be a waste of your time
and attention.
150:
You told me to do whatever I
wanted, Father. I'm doing just that.
153:
I can continue working at the
Academy while helping out my
original family. I even get to keep
adventuring with Alk and the others!
155:
Oh... Father? Don't tell me you
WANTED me to leave the Academy
to join them!
159: Glad you two get along so well.
166:
All right, well, I'm off into town. I'll be
home in the evening.
172:
Of course I am. I'm surrounded by
kind souls on all sides, after all.
